@startuml Sequence_PasswordReset

title Sequenzdiagramm - Passwort-Reset (Admin-basiert, Ist-Implementierung)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor "Student" as Student
actor "Administrator" as Admin
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "AuthServlet" as AuthServlet
participant "AuthService" as AuthService
participant "UserDao" as UserDao
participant "AdminServlet" as AdminServlet
participant "PasswordUtils" as PasswordUtils
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

== Schritt 1: Student stellt Reset-Anfrage ==

Student -> FE : "Passwort vergessen" klicken
FE -> AuthServlet : POST /api/auth/reset-request\n{username}

AuthServlet -> AuthService : requestPasswordReset(username)
AuthService -> UserDao : findByUsername(username)
UserDao -> DB : SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE username = ?
DB --> UserDao : User oder none

alt User nicht gefunden
    UserDao --> AuthService : Optional.empty()
    AuthService --> AuthServlet : IllegalArgumentException\n"User not found"
    AuthServlet --> FE : HTTP 400\n{error: "User not found"}
    FE --> Student : Fehlermeldung
else User gefunden
    UserDao --> AuthService : Optional<User>
    AuthService -> UserDao : setPasswordResetRequested(userId, true)
    UserDao -> DB : UPDATE users\nSET reset_requested = true\nWHERE id = ?
    DB --> UserDao : OK
    AuthService --> AuthServlet : ok
    AuthServlet --> FE : HTTP 200\n{status: "ok"}
    FE --> Student : Bestätigung
end

== Schritt 2: Admin bearbeitet Reset-Anfragen ==

Admin -> FE : Admin-Panel öffnen
FE -> AdminServlet : GET /api/admin/users/requests

AdminServlet -> UserDao : findPasswordResetRequests()
UserDao -> DB : SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE reset_requested = true
DB --> UserDao : List<User>
UserDao --> AdminServlet : List<User>
AdminServlet --> FE : HTTP 200\nJSON [{id, username, resetRequested, ...}]
FE --> Admin : Liste anzeigen

alt Admin genehmigt und setzt Passwort
    Admin -> FE : Neues Passwort eingeben
    FE -> AdminServlet : PUT /api/admin/users\n{id, password, resetComplete: true}

    AdminServlet -> UserDao : findById(id)
    UserDao -> DB : SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE id = ?
    DB --> UserDao : User
    UserDao --> AdminServlet : User

    AdminServlet -> PasswordUtils : generateSaltHex()
    PasswordUtils --> AdminServlet : salt
    AdminServlet -> PasswordUtils : hashPassword(password, salt)
    PasswordUtils --> AdminServlet : hash

    AdminServlet -> UserDao : update(user)\n(set hash/salt, reset_requested=false)
    UserDao -> DB : UPDATE users\nSET password_hash=?, password_salt=?,\n    reset_requested=false\nWHERE id = ?
    DB --> UserDao : OK
    AdminServlet --> FE : HTTP 200\n{status: "ok"}
else Admin lehnt ab (schließt Request)
    FE -> AdminServlet : PUT /api/admin/users\n{id, resetComplete: true}
    AdminServlet -> UserDao : update(user)\n(reset_requested=false)
    UserDao -> DB : UPDATE users\nSET reset_requested=false\nWHERE id = ?
    DB --> UserDao : OK
    AdminServlet --> FE : HTTP 200\n{status: "ok"}
end

note over Admin, Student
    **Keine Email-Funktion:**
    Admin teilt das neue Passwort manuell mit.
end note

@enduml
